---
import Layout from "../Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import HeaderHero from "../components/HeaderHero.astro";
import WaitListForm from "../components/WaitListForm.astro";
import Button from "../components/elements/Button.astro";
import Card from "../components/elements/Card.astro";
import Grid from "../components/elements/Grid.astro";
import Heading from "../components/elements/Heading.astro";
import Paragraph from "../components/elements/Paragraph.astro";
import SVG from "../components/elements/SVG.astro";
import Section from "../components/elements/Section.astro";

const {
	headerColor1 = "rgba(150, 140, 150, 0.1)",
	headerColor2 = "rgba(150, 40, 50, 0.0)",
	headerColor3 = "rgba(150, 150, 150, 0.1)",
	linearColor1 = "rgba(150, 40, 50, 0.1)",
	background = "linear-gradient(135deg, #f0f7e522, #f0f0f522);",
} = Astro.props || {};
---

<Layout
  title="About Mermind"
  description="Learn more about Mermind"
  canonicalUrl={`${Astro.site}about`}
>
  <Header color1={headerColor1} color2={headerColor2} color3={headerColor3} linearColor1={linearColor1} background={background}>
    <HeaderHero
      paddingY="lg"
      altTitle="Who We Are"
      title="We saw a gap that should not exist"
      lead="Mermind is built by people who have worked inside real e-commerce operations — and kept running into the same problem. Not a lack of data. A lack of understanding."
      variant="default"
      size="default"
    >
    <div slot="graphic">
        <SVG size="100%">
          <path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"></path>
          <path d="M16 3.128a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.744"></path>
          <path d="M22 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"></path>
          <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"></circle>
        </SVG>
      </div>
    </HeaderHero>
  </Header>
	<main>
    <Section>
      <div slot="header" class="section--header">
        <div class="alt-title">Where It Started</div>
        <Heading level={2} size="xl">The problem is not new. The solution is.</Heading>
        <Paragraph size="lg" dimmed>We did not need more dashboards. We needed a system that understands.</Paragraph>
      </div>
      <Grid columns={1} gap="2rem">
        <Card>
          <div>
            <Paragraph>Every operator who has run a serious e-commerce operation has had the same experience. Something breaks quietly — a listing goes down, tracking stops firing, a margin slowly erodes. Nobody notices until the numbers move. By then, the cost is already paid.</Paragraph>
            <p>This is not a gap in effort or attention. It is a gap in infrastructure. No system was built to watch your operation the way it needs to be watched — continuously, across all your tools, with no commercial stake in what the answer is.</p>
            <p>The tools were built to report. So teams spend their time reconstructing what happened instead of preventing what is coming.</p>
            <p>Mermind exists to close that gap. We did not need more dashboards. We needed a system that understands.</p>
          </div>
        </Card>
        <Card>
          <Heading level={3} size="lg">Mission</Heading>
          <Paragraph margin="sm" size="lg">To build a neutral operational intelligence layer that helps e-commerce teams understand what is happening in their operations, prevent what should not happen, and act with clarity at every stage of growth.</Paragraph>
        </Card>
      </Grid>
    </Section>
    <Section>
      <div slot="header" class="section--header">
        <div class="alt-title">How We Build</div>
        <Heading level={2} size="2xl">Our Values</Heading>
        <Paragraph size="lg">We would rather do one thing correctly than many things approximately. A system that is sometimes wrong about important things is not a better tool — it is noise that costs you decisions. We start narrow and expand only when the foundation is proven.</Paragraph>
      </div>
      <Grid columns={2} gap="2rem">
        <Card>
          <div class="icon">
            <SVG size="48" dimmed>
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"></circle>
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"></circle>
            </SVG>
          </div>
          <Heading level={3}>Accuracy Over Breadth</Heading>
          <Paragraph>We would rather do one thing correctly than many things approximately. A system that is sometimes wrong about important things is not a better tool — it is noise that costs you decisions. We start narrow and expand only when the foundation is proven.</Paragraph>
        </Card>
        <Card>
          <div class="icon">
            <SVG size="48" dimmed>
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
              <path d="M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3"></path>
              <path d="M12 17h.01"></path>
            </SVG>
          </div>
          <Heading level={3}>Explanation Before Action</Heading>
          <Paragraph>Mermind will not surface a recommendation it cannot explain. Every insight has a traceable reason. Every alert has a clear cause. This is not a feature — it is the architectural principle that makes the intelligence trustworthy.</Paragraph>
        </Card>
        <Card>
          <div class="icon">
            <SVG size="48" dimmed>
              <path d="M19.414 14.414C21 12.828 22 11.5 22 9.5a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-9.591-3.676.6.6 0 0 1-.818.001A5.5 5.5 0 0 0 2 9.5c0 2.3 1.5 4 3 5.5l5.535 5.362a2 2 0 0 0 2.879.052 2.12 2.12 0 0 0-.004-3 2.124 2.124 0 1 0 3-3 2.124 2.124 0 0 0 3.004 0 2 2 0 0 0 0-2.828l-1.881-1.882a2.41 2.41 0 0 0-3.409 0l-1.71 1.71a2 2 0 0 1-2.828 0 2 2 0 0 1 0-2.828l2.823-2.762"></path>
            </SVG>
          </div>
          <Heading level={3}>Earn Trust, Don't Assume It</Heading>
          <Paragraph>Trust in a system is built through demonstrated accuracy over time, not through a promise at onboarding. Mermind starts with a narrow scope, proves its judgment on real operational problems, and earns a broader role only as that trust compounds.</Paragraph>
        </Card>
        <Card>
          <div class="icon">
            <SVG size="48" dimmed>
              <path d="M12 6v16"></path>
              <path d="m19 13 2-1a9 9 0 0 1-18 0l2 1"></path>
              <path d="M9 11h6"></path>
              <circle cx="12" cy="4" r="2"></circle>
            </SVG>
          </div>
          <Heading level={3}>Reliability as a Foundation</Heading>
          <Paragraph>Intelligence that operators cannot depend on consistently is not intelligence — it is a liability. We treat reliability as the non-negotiable foundation everything else is built on, not a future milestone.</Paragraph>
        </Card>
      </Grid>
    </Section>
    <Section bg="stripes" centered>
      <div slot="header" class="section--header">
        <div class="alt-title">Where We Are</div>
        <Heading level={2} size="2xl">Current Status</Heading>
        <Paragraph size="lg">Mermind is in early development. We are building a narrow, reliable foundation before expanding into broader capabilities. This means fewer features, more accuracy, and a deliberate sequence that does not skip foundational steps.</Paragraph>
      </div>
    </Section>
    <Section>
      <div slot="header" class="section--header">
        <div class="alt-title">Get Early Access</div>
        <Heading level={2} size="2xl">Be part of the journey</Heading>
        <Paragraph size="lg">Mermind is evolving step by step. Join the waitlist to stay informed and gain early access.</Paragraph>
      </div>
      <Card padding="lg" outlined>
        <Heading level={3} size="lg">Join the Waitlist</Heading>
        <Paragraph>
          Join the waitlist to follow along and be among the first to experience Mermind.
        </Paragraph>
        <WaitListForm />
      </Card>
    </Section>
  </main>
</Layout>
